commit.message:
[CMake] Improved Lua detection - #808

The default Lua version on many systems is often newer than 5.1
However, such versions seem to be incompatible with OLX.
So search first for "lua5.1" and if it's not found,
search for "lua-5.1" - this works on Fedora, for example.
If neither is found, search for "lua" and finally use default "lua"
but give warnings and suggestions too because errors may be likely.

Merge pull request #794 from lxkurko/0.59

Fixes and additions for 0.59

Check weapon selection time when immediate start is on

Max weapon selection time is now enforced when immediate
start is enabled. However, the warning message is not displayed
when immediate start is on. This could be fixed, but it would
be annoying for those who are already playing. A better solution
would be to explicitly check whether each player is playing or
still selecting weapons.

Configurable killing/dying spree thresholds

Thresholds for killing/dying sprees can now be configured.

Option to reduce logging

By default, OLX used to log all chat messages to the main log
when hosting a server. This cluttered the log and didn't provide
very useful information. Now logging can be turned off.

Check chat message length

OLX allows sending arbitrarily long chat messages.
Long messages can cause excessive lag and annoyance.
Check chat message length, truncate oversized messages
and optionally kick the sender.

Check nick length

Check nick length server-side when joining, sending wants to join messages
or using setmyname command, and truncate oversized nicks.
0.58 allows creation of excessively long nicknames that cause
lots of annoyance.

Join glitch fix

Fixed the "empty name join glitch".
